【One Pot Mushroom Rice】⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
Easy peasy mushroom rice made in one pot using Mayer rice cooker. Really! Even the rice gets cooked right in!⁣ Love to prepare meal in rice cooker which is able to feed my always-hungry kids on time during this circuit break period.😂⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
INGREDIENTS (for 2 pax)⁣⁣⁣
▫️Uncooked rice⁣⁣⁣
▫️Boneless chicken drumstick, sliced ⁣⁣⁣
▫️2 cloves garlic, minced⁣⁣⁣
▫️2 big shiitake mushroom @mushroomkingdom_sg , sliced⁣⁣⁣
▫️Carrots, sliced⁣⁣⁣
▫️1 tbsp dark soy sauce ⁣⁣⁣
▫️1 tbsp oyster sauce ⁣⁣⁣
▫️1/2 cup water⁣⁣⁣
▫️Chopped spring onion ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
Chicken marinate:⁣⁣⁣
▫️1 tbsp light soy sauce⁣⁣⁣
▫️1 tsp sesame oil⁣⁣⁣
▫️1 tsp @liloikanbilis mushroom powder ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
INSTRUCTIONS ⁣⁣⁣
1️⃣Marinate chicken with seasoning as mentioned above for 15 minutes.⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
2️⃣Heat the pan and sauté garlic until fragrant.⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
3️⃣Add chicken into pan and fry until it is cooked.⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
4️⃣Add in dark soy sauce, oyster sauce and water and bring to boil.⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
5️⃣Add mushroom powder to add umami taste.⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
6️⃣Add in mushroom and carrot. Mix well and cook for 1-2 minutes. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
7️⃣Transfer everything into the bowl of a rice cooker. Hit the START button and start to cook. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
8️⃣Once cooked, serve immediately and garnished with chopped spring onion.⁣⁣⁣
⁣
